# Valgrind suppressions for navi's leak check.
#
# Scope: we run with --show-leak-kinds=definite,indirect and treat only those as
# errors, so OpenSSL's process-global "still reachable" caches and "possibly
# lost" interior pointers are already ignored without suppressions. Entries here
# are for the residual *definite/indirect* leaks that are genuinely not navi's
# to free (one-time library/loader initialization). Keep this list short and
# specific; a navi-owned leak must be fixed, not suppressed.

# One-time dynamic-loader init when the first dlopen'd codec/TLS lib is resolved.
{
  dl-init-once
  Memcheck:Leak
  match-leak-kinds: definite,indirect
  ...
  fun:_dl_init
}
